<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='835423' id='t-835423'>Desmond Tutu talks
about the concept of ubuntu,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='840382' id='t-840382'>in the context of South Africa's
Truth and Reconciliation process</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='844061' id='t-844061'>that they embarked on after apartheid.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='846378' id='t-846378'>He says it means,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='848737' id='t-848737'>&quot;My humanity is caught up,
is inextricably bound up, in yours;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='854287' id='t-854287'>we belong to a bundle of life.&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='860381' id='t-860381'>A bundle of life.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='864019' id='t-864019'>The Truth and Reconciliation process</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='865831' id='t-865831'>started by elevating
the voices of the unheard.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='870068' id='t-870068'>If this country is going to live up to its
promise of liberty and justice for all,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='876033' id='t-876033'>then we need to elevate
the voices of our unheard,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='879146' id='t-879146'>of people like Jobana,
Sintia and Bertha,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='882651' id='t-882651'>Theresa and Baakir.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='885809' id='t-885809'>We must leverage their solutions
and their ideas.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='889437' id='t-889437'>We must listen to their true stories,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='892591' id='t-892591'>their more beautifully complex stories.</span>
</span>
</p>
